reviews.text: This is a nice station, but the very important is the people workers here! On my first trip to London, I could not contact the host of Airbnb for my first stay, and the employees of this station gave me strong support and helped to establish that contact.  I send a big greeting and recognition to David!  everyone here was available to provide support !.  excellent team!

A really tidy and well looked after station, another plus for TFL
Good accessibility and staff on site
Waiting room area and plenty of places to sit down
All that and a good reliable train service what more could you ask for

Just moved to the area, quiet station with staff and a waiting area. All that doesn't matter when the East bound trains are late by 3-5 minutes 100% of the time during the week day peak. Also a very large gap to mind that I've seen people have trouble with
End of the Gospel Oak to Barking Line. Still awaiting new longer trains after 2 years.
Unassuming little station that kinda creeps up on you out of nowhere, but once you know it exists, there's no turning back. Indispensable
